heaviest_rainfall.status: The most intense rainfall recorded took place on 04 January 2025, with precipitation totalling 36.8mm.  The rain fell at 4.6mm per hour at times over the course of the 37.2 hour storm.

heaviest_rainrate.status: Today, the rain fell at an intense rate peaking at 10.1mm per hour, one of the heaviest downpours recorded and ranked 10th from our records.  The precipitation lasted 16.6 hours and dumped 9.37mm in total.  The heaviest rain rate registered stands at 27.0mm per hour on 02 September 2025, highlighting an extreme precipitation event.  21.19mm fell during the storm over 15.0 hours.

longest_rain.status: Today's rainstorm ranked 10th on our record table for the length of the storm as it lasted 16.6 hours; it delivered 9.37mm of rain at a maximum rate of 10.1mm per hour.  Rain fell for 37.2 hours on 04 January 2025 creating a new record that still lasts.  The storm produced a total of 36.8mm with a maximum intensity of 4.6mm per hour.
